        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 1:19PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Widespread showers and thunderstorms are developing this afternoon
and slowly drifting off to the east at around 15 to 20 MPH. While
severe winds or hail are not expected, some of the storms may
still produce gusty outflow winds to 40 mph and pea to half inch
sized hail. In addition, heavy rain will also be possible with
some of the storms, and with the slow storm movement some ponding
of water in low lying and poor drainage areas is possible.
</description>
